(thirdQuint)Study of Equivalence of Generic Pimecrolimus Cream 1% and Elidel 1% in Subjects With Mild to Moderate Atopic Dermatitis.

 Pimecrolimus cream, 1% is a calcineurin inhibitor immunosuppressant.

 Pimecrolimus inhibits T cell activation by blocking the transcription of early cytokines.

 Pimecrolimus cream, 1% is indicated as second-line therapy for the short-term and non-continuous chronic treatment of mild-to-moderate atopic dermatitis in non-immunocompromised adults and children 2 years of age and older who have failed to respond adequately to other topical prescription treatments, or when those treatments are not advisable.

 This study is being conducted to evaluate the clinical bioequivalence of sponsor's formulation of Pimecrolimus Cream, 1%, the Test product, and Elidel Cream, 1%, the Reference product.

 A vehicle control arm is included to demonstrate that the Test and Reference products are active and to establish that the study is sufficiently sensitive to detect differences between products.

